ning eleven years later, he opened his first column, as I was saying when I was so rudely interrupted.","number":3},{"category":"military","header":"He covered the war from carriers and gliders","body":"During the Second World War Woodward set sports aside to report as a war correspondent. He rode with the 101st Airborne into the Netherlands and sailed with Task Force 58 off Iwo Jima.","number":4}],"sources":[],"institutions":[{"institution_id":"INST018","relationship":"alumnus","years":"1913-1917","institution_blurb":"Played tackle for the Amherst football team."}],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"research_tags":[],"cross_connections":[{"type":"historical_connection","related_id":"X00126","display_label":"helped found Yale, one of the colleges Woodward dubbed ivy"},{"type":"historical_connection","related_id":"X00613","display_label":"led Princeton, one of the colleges Woodward dubbed ivy"},{"type":"parallel_careers","related_id":"HD5949","display_label":"the Hall of Fame high-school basketball coach"}],"quotes":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"statues":[],"bio":{"first_name":"Rufus Stanley","last_name":"Woodward","display_name":"Stanley Woodward","gender":"male","married_names":[],"photo_url":"https://res.cloudinary.com/dc5clrqtw/image/upload/v1780795180/Rufus_Stanley_Woodward_1895-1965_mlnmz5.png"},"military_service":[],"education":[{"institution_id":"INST018","type":"college","dates":"1913-1917"}],"career":[{"role":"Sports Editor","organization":"New York Herald Tribune","start_year":1938,"end_year":1962}],"slug":"rufus-stanley-woodward-1895"},"I01582":{"id":"I01582","former_ids":[],"is_placeholder":false,"has_descendants_documented":false,"gender":"female","classification":{"is_thomas_descendant":false,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_thomas_spouse":true,"include_in_path_calculation":false,"is_easter_egg":false},"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"parents":{},"number_of_marriages":1,"marriages":[{"spouse_id":"HD5928","children_ids":[]}],