, Connecticut, near her home. Children watched from the foot of the scaffolding as she hid a dragonfly and a mouse for them to find.","number":3},{"category":"career","header":"A Boston illustrator drew her into books","body":"Trained at the Museum of Fine Arts School in Boston and in Paris, Woodward was introduced to book illustration by the artist Marguerite Davis. Her first commission came in 1931, and she filled her apple-orchard house with visiting children ever after.","number":4}],"sources":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"research_tags":[],"cross_connections":[],"quotes":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"statues":[],"bio":{"first_name":"Hildegard H.","last_name":"Woodward","display_name":"Hildegard H. Woodward","gender":"female","married_names":[]},"military_service":[],"education":[{"school_name":"School of the Museum of Fine Arts, Boston","type":"art_school"},{"school_name":"Paris (independent study)","type":"art_study"}],"career":[{"role":"Children's-book illustrator and author","start_year":1931,"end_year":1977}],"slug":"hildegard-h-woodward-1898"},"HD5930":{"id":"HD5930","former_ids":[],"is_placeholder":false,"has_descendants_documented":false,"gender":"female","birth":{"year":1900,"country":"United States"},"death":{"year":1979,"country":"United States"},"classification":{"is_thomas_descendant":true,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"include_in_path_calculation":true,"is_easter_egg":false,"generation_from_thomas":10},"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"parents":{"father_id":"HD5926","mother_id":"I01581"},"number_of_marriages":0,"marriages":[],"tags":[],"narrative_blocks":[],"sources":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"research_tags":[],"cross_connections":[],"quotes":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"statues":[],"bio":{"first_name":"Katherine Fox","last_name":"Woodward","display_name":"Katherine Fox Woodward","gender":"female","married_names":[]},"military_service":[],"education":[],"slug":"